definition.value: Surgical procedures performed on bone.
Surgical repair of bone.
Any surgical procedure that results in the construction or reconstruction of bone.
Any surgical procedure that results in the construction or reconstruction of the pelvic bone.
Pelvic osteoplasty performed for the purposes of feminization, especially for transgender women and transfeminine persons.

Note that "bar rag" was initially considered a pejorative term.

A typically brief, unspecified temporal interval.
Note that a "moment" was a specific unit of time during the Medieval Period in Europe, representing one-tenth of a point, or one-fortieth or one-fiftieth of an hour.
A moment in history which is said to be of some importance, or a contemporary moment which is theorized to have such importance.
A moment in LGBTQ history which is said to be of some importance, or a contemporary LGBTQ moment which is theorized to have such importance.
A moment in transgender history which is said to be of some importance, or a contemporary transgender moment which is theorized to have such importance.

A relationship in which at least one partner is bisexual and at least one partner is a lesbian.
A relationship in which at least one partner is bisexual and at least one partner is a gay man.
A relationship in which at least one partner is bisexual and at least one partner is heterosexual.

A relationship involving some kind of sexual intimacy between at least two people in which all parties are gay men.
A relationship involving some kind of sexual intimacy between at least two people in which all parties are lesbians.

Any of various magazines devoted to physique photography, photography of typically young and attractive muscular men in athletic poses, usually in revealing minimal clothing.
Pants utilized in sexual bondage.
Any of various events involving cross-dressing and ballroom dancing.
Any of various lesbian events involving ballroom dancing.

Magnus Hirschfeld mentioned such balls in his book Berlins drittes Geschlect (1904): "In a big hall, where the uranians celebrate their balls, every week there is an equivalent evening ball for uranierinnen, most of whom participate in men's clothing. Most homosexual women can be found at the same spot every year on the costume ball a lady from Berlin organizes. The ball is not public, but usually only accessible those that are known to one of the ladies on the committee."
Any of various gay male events involving ballroom dancing.
The action or fact of making a specified thing smaller or less in amount, degree, or size.
Lessening of negative social and/or physical consequences associated with various human behaviors, both legal and illegal.

The application of methods designed to reduce the risk of harm associated with certain behaviors without reduction in frequency of those behaviors. The risk-associated behaviors include ongoing and active addictive behaviors.
Any of various policies which are meant to achieve any of various healthcare outcomes.
Any of various policies which are meant to achieve any of various public health outcomes.
Any of various policies which are meant to achieve any of various mental health outcomes.

Any of various public health policies designed to lessen the negative social and/or physical consequences associated with various human behaviors, both legal and illegal. Harm reduction policies are used to manage behaviors such as recreational drug use and sexual activity in numerous settings that range from services through to geographical regions.
Misconduct in relationship to the processes of research, including, but not limited to: fabrication, falsification, and plagiarism.
A branch of separatist feminism which advocates for separation of heterosexual women from patriarchal society in general.
A bisexual person is a lesbian.
